# Creating Cursor Rules

## When to Create
- Pattern repeats >3 times
- Prevents documented anti-pattern
- Enforces measurable standard

## Structure
```markdown
---
description: Brief purpose
globs: ["relevant/paths/**"]
---
# Rule Name

Core instruction in 1-3 sentences.

**Enforcement**: Specific check/pattern
```

## Placement
- 000-099: Meta rules
- 100-199: Git/version control
- 200-299: Structure/standards
- 300-399: Configuration patterns
- 400-499: Security/secrets
- 500+: Workflows

## Token Budget
- Target: 250-350 tokens
- Maximum: 500 tokens
- Total limit: 4000 tokens across all rules
- If >500 tokens needed â†’ documentation, not rule

## Keep Minimal
- <150 words
- One enforceable concept
- Examples only if non-obvious
- Reference line numbers in docs when applicable
